UDoS for GNU/Linux - Universal DoS and DDoS testing tool

Usage: udos [option] [long GNU option]

Valid options:
  -h, --help             : display this help
  -f, --fork             : fork to background
  -d, --debug            : switch to debug log level
  -s, --socket           : use TCP or UDP connection over ethernet/wireless, default TCP, available TCP, UDP, RFC (bluetooth)
  -t, --target           : target adress (bluetooth mac or ip adress over ethernet/wireless)
  -p, --port             : destination port
  -b, --bytes            : number of bytes to send in one packet

Examples:
udos -s TCP -t 1.1.1.1 -p 80 -b 256 # TCP flood 1.1.1.1:80 with 256 byte packets
udos -s UDP -t 2.2.2.2 -p 21 -b 1024 # UDP flood 2.2.2.2:21 with 1024 byte packets
udos -s RFC -t 00:11:22:33:44 -b 668 # Bluetooth ping flood 00:11:22:33:44 with 668 byte packets
udos -s HTTP -t http://localhost/index.php # HTTP GET flood on localhost, make many index.php requests as possible

